<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-08-09T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-08-09T10:00:00-05:00" n="743" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d743">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.<gloss target="#t_CC1">CC</gloss> (<gloss target="#t_PC1">PC</gloss>)/8–945:
                                    Telegram</note>
                                <head>No. 743<lb/><hi rend="italic">The Alternate Delegate to the
                                        Preparatory Commission of the United Nations</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GOB1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gerig</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Director of
                                        the Office of Special Political Affairs</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_HA2" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Hiss</hi></persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d743fn1">Sent to
                                        the Secretary of State over the signature of <persName corresp="#p_WJG2">Winant</persName>.</note></head>
                                <opener>
                                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]</seg>
                                </opener>
                                <opener>
                                    <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi></seg>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-08-09T16:00:00+01:00">August 9, 1945—4
                                            p.m.</date></dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p>8019. For <persName corresp="#p_HA2">Hiss</persName> from
                                        <persName corresp="#p_GOB1">Gerig</persName>.</p>
                                <p>Your <gloss target="#t_Preco1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Preco</hi></gloss> 23,<note n="2" xml:id="d743fn2"><ref target="#d742">Document No. 742</ref>.</note>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_JG1">Jebb</persName> informs he discussed
                                    question of officers <gloss target="#t_ExCom1">ExCom</gloss>
                                    (Executive Committee) and <gloss target="#t_PreCo1">PreCo</gloss> (Preparatory Committee) on margin of Potsdam
                                    conference with <persName corresp="#p_DJC1">Dunn</persName>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_GAA1">Gromyko</persName> and others and
                                    that rotation principle for <gloss target="#t_ExCom1">ExCom</gloss> was suggested for consideration. Soviet group
                                    seemed favorable but have not yet replied definitely;…</p>
                            </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>